# [emoji type]: [subject]
#
# [body]
#
# [footer]
#
# Type can be:
# - 🎉 init: initial commit
# - ✨ feat: new feature
# - 🛠️ fix: bug fix
# - 📝 docs: documentation changes (README, site content, etc.)
# - 💄 style: formatting, whitespace, linting – no logic change
# - ♻️ refactor: code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# - ⚡️ perf: performance improvements
# - ✅ test: add or update tests
# - 🧪 testdata: add or update mock/test data or fixtures
# - 🧹 chore: maintenance tasks (gitignore, cleanup, etc.)
# - ⚙️ config: configuration files (eslint, tailwind, vscode, env)
# - 📦 assets: static files (images, icons, fonts)
# - 🔄 ci: CI/CD config or pipeline changes
# - 🏗️ build: build tools or dependencies
# - 🔥 remove: remove code, files, or packages
# - 🚚 move: move or rename files
# - 🛑 revert: revert a previous commit
# - 🚨 lint: fix lint warnings/errors
# - 🚧 wip: work in progress (temporary commits)
# - 📌 deps: dependency changes (upgrade, downgrade, pin)
# - 🔐 security: security fixes
# - 🧰 tooling: custom dev tools or scripts
# - 🗃️ db: database schema, migration, or seed
# - 🧑‍💻 dev: developer environment setup (Docker, SDKs)
# - 🎩 update: small polish, tweaks, or minor changes

# Subject: 50 chars max, present tense, lowercase
# Body: Wrap at 72 chars. Explain what and why, not how
# Footer: Reference issues, breaking changes, co-authors, etc.
